(# DrainGuard Project Documentation) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 1. Project Title) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(**DrainGuard: Smart Urban Drainage Issue Management System**) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 2. Project Overview) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(DrainGuard is a PHP/MySQL role-based urban drainage issue management system. It digitizes) Tj
T*
(drainage complaint submission, review, ward routing, maintenance assignment, proof upload,) Tj
T*
(inspector verification, citizen feedback, objection handling, notifications, audit/status logs,) Tj
T*
(and high-risk area detection.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The inspected project uses PHP, MySQLi, MySQL/MariaDB, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Bootstrap,) Tj
T*
(Bootstrap Icons, and XAMPP. No React, Laravel, Tailwind, PDO, or framework-based stack was) Tj
T*
(found.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The system is designed for municipal drainage operations. Citizens report problems, central) Tj
T*
(officers review and route complaints, ward officers verify local responsibility and assign) Tj
T*
(teams, maintenance teams perform the work, and inspectors verify completion before closure.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 3. Problem Statement) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Manual drainage complaint management creates these problems:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Slow complaint handling because reports are forwarded manually.) Tj
T*
(- No clear real-time tracking for citizens.) Tj
T*
(- Weak accountability because responsible users and decisions are not recorded in a structured) Tj
T*
(way.) Tj
T*
(- Difficulty routing complaints to the correct city corporation, thana, ward, and area.) Tj
T*
(- Difficulty verifying actual work completion without uploaded proof and inspection.) Tj
T*
(- Lack of structured notification across citizen, central, ward, maintenance, and inspector) Tj
T*
(roles.) Tj
T*
(- Lack of audit/status logs for judging progress and responsibility.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(DrainGuard solves these problems by storing the full complaint lifecycle in a relational) Tj
T*
(database and by giving every role a clear workflow.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 4. Project Objective) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The main objectives are:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Digital complaint submission.) Tj
T*
(- Real-time complaint tracking through database statuses and logs.) Tj
T*
(- Role-wise workflow and authorization.) Tj
T*
(- Correct routing by city corporation, ward, area, location, and drain.) Tj
T*
(- Maintenance team assignment and change support.) Tj
T*
(- Proof-based work completion using image/video uploads.) Tj
T*
(- Inspector verification before final closure.) Tj
T*
(- Citizen feedback and objection after closure.) Tj
T*
(- Role-wise notification delivery.) Tj
T*
(- High-risk area detection from complaint frequency, affected area, urgency, and repeated) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
