(## 20. Testing / Demo Data) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The SQL dump contains development/demo users, complaints, notifications, reports, and upload) Tj
T*
(paths. The system also has role creation pages for adding test officers, teams, and members.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(A judge can test the project with this flow:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Login as a citizen.) Tj
T*
(2. Submit a complaint with location, issue, affected area, description, and optional media.) Tj
T*
(3. Check Public Complaint Board, My Complaints, Track Complaint, and citizen notifications.) Tj
T*
(4. Login as Central Officer.) Tj
T*
(5. Accept the complaint and route it to a ward.) Tj
T*
(6. Login as the assigned Ward Officer.) Tj
T*
(7. Verify the complaint and assign a maintenance team.) Tj
T*
(8. Login as maintenance team leader/member.) Tj
T*
(9. Start work, optionally request support, and upload completion proof.) Tj
T*
(10. Login as Inspector.) Tj
T*
(11. Review before/after proof and approve work or mark false completion.) Tj
T*
(12. Login again as Citizen.) Tj
T*
(13. Submit feedback or objection.) Tj
T*
(14. Check notifications and complaint tracking after each step.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## 21. Limitations) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- The project is local unless deployed and configured on a live server.) Tj
T*
(- No GPS/map integration was found in the inspected files.) Tj
T*
(- Notifications are system/database-based, not SMS-based.) Tj
T*
(- Email support is present for password reset through PHPMailer, but workflow notifications are) Tj
T*
(mainly in-system.) Tj
T*
(- Real-time tracking may require refresh or polling unless a WebSocket layer is added later.) Tj
T*
(- Risk detection is rule/frequency-based, not AI-based.) Tj
T*
(- Analytics can be expanded further.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
